raw_mentions: As used herein, by "agonist", or "activating compound", or "activator", "exhibiting agonist activity" or the like, is meant those compounds which have a pKi of at least 6.0 (preferably at least 7.0) to the relevant PPAR, for example hPPAR delta, in the binding assay described below, and which achieve at least 30% (preferably at least 50%) activation of the relevant PPAR relative to the appropriate indicated positive control in the transfection assay described below at concentrations of 25 10^"5 M or less (preferably 10^"6 M or less).
